    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "t_start": 0.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 7.0,
      "narration_text": "A quantum state called 'stationary' \u2014 nothing moves. Or so it seems.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "QUANTUM MECHANICS",
        "headline": "Why a Stationary State Isn't Standing Still",
        "sub": "The invisible spin"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 4.31,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-stationary-phase/clips/B01.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B01.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "t_start": 7.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "One energy eigenstate: its probability cloud is frozen. Completely flat. Nothing changes. The phasor spins \u2014 but you cannot see it.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "note": "Single phasor arrow rotating in complex plane, |\u03c8|\u00b2 bar flat on right panel",
      "audio_file": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.67,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-stationary-phase/clips/B02.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B02.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "t_start": 17.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "But atoms emit light at sharp frequencies. If stationary states don't oscillate, where do the spectral lines come from?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "THE QUESTION",
        "headline": "If a stationary state never oscillates,\nwhere do spectral lines come from?",
        "sub": null
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 6.82,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-stationary-phase/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "t_start": 26.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "Classically, a vibrating charge radiates at its oscillation frequency. A static charge radiates nothing. A frozen electron should be silent.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "note": "Classical: oscillating charge emits (arrow), static dot emits nothing (X)",
      "audio_file": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.86,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-stationary-phase/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "t_start": 35.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "One eigenstate: |\u03c8|\u00b2 is flat in time. The phase rotates at E/\u210f \u2014 but |e^{-iEt/\u210f}| = 1. The rotation is invisible. There is nothing to see.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "note": "Single phasor at E1 rotating; probability density panel stays flat/constant",
      "audio_file": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.58,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-stationary-phase/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "t_start": 45.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 6.0,
      "narration_text": "Superpose two energies.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "THE MECHANISM",
        "headline": "Two phases beat at the Bohr frequency",
        "sub": "f = (E\u2082 \u2212 E\u2081) / h"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 1.57,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-stationary-phase/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "t_start": 51.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 13.0,
      "narration_text": "Add state 1 and state 2. Each phase rotates at its own rate. Their difference rotates at (E\u2082 \u2212 E\u2081)/\u210f \u2014 the Bohr frequency. The cross term in |\u03c8|\u00b2 oscillates at exactly that rate.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "note": "Two phasors E1 and E2 rotating; difference vector oscillates; |\u03c8|\u00b2 panel shows sloshing",
      "audio_file": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 15.12,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-stationary-phase/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "t_start": 64.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "narration_text": "The probability cloud rocks back and forth. The electron's center of charge oscillates. An oscillating charge radiates \u2014 at frequency (E\u2082 \u2212 E\u2081)/h. That is the spectral line.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "slosh"
      },
      "note": "Probability density rocking left-right; emission arrow out; frequency label",
      "audio_file": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.79,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-stationary-phase/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-stationary-phase/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "t_start": 75.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 5.0,
      "narration_text": "Every spectral line, the same story.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "THE IMPLICATION",
        "headline": "Every spectral line is a beating pair of phases",
